						               													<description>Five Battles from the Arab-Israeli Conflict, scenarios for Modern Armor&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These scenarios are based on five iconic armor actions during the Arab-Israeli conflicts, between 1956 and 1982.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Various liberties have been taken with the historical actions to reduce large, complex battles to a tabletop game, and various vehicles have been used that probably were not present together on this particular battlefield, but saw action in the same theatre of war. An example is the inclusion of the AMX-13 in the Operation Kadesh scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These scenarios were included (in condensed form) in the Modern Armor rulebook.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Suez Crisis &amp;mdash; Operation Kadesh&amp;#10;     The Six-Day War &amp;mdash; Sharon at Umm Qatef&amp;#10;     Yom Kippur War &amp;mdash; The Chinese Farm&amp;#10;     Yom Kippur War &amp;mdash; The Heights of Courage&amp;#10;     Operation Peace in Galilee &amp;mdash; Soultane Yacoub&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each scenarios contains:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Historical information on units and deployment suitable for use with any micro-armor system.&amp;#10;     Unit statistics and scenario rules for Modern Armor&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
